args: Please note that this story contains spoilers\nfor the Fractured Futures event.
Something up, chum? You look like you're\nreally working the ol' noodle there.
I was just thinking about Audric.
And about the world we visited.
You mean our possible future or whatever?
Yeah, that's what Audric said about it.\nIn that world, we had lost our fight and\nthe Empire ruled over everything.
Yeesh, man. Mondo bad vibes.\nI don't wanna believe it.
I feel the same way. But I just can't\nforget what I saw.
That's why I'm so worried about it.\nI can't stop thinking about how things\nare going in that world right now.
And about how Audric is doing...
Keep your wits about you, everyone!\nDragons of the Empire approach!
Blast it all, this position is lost...\nEveryone, fall back inside the castle walls!
Weathering a continued assault by\nnumbers of this magnitude will make\neven retreat a difficult proposition.
Then I shall hold them here and buy time\nfor the rest of you to escape!
Ah, my old friend... I'm so sorry...\nEveryone, make for the castle now!
Did everybody make it out in one piece?
Would that it were so—but I fear we have\nagain sustained significant losses.
Additionally, we'll not be able to hold\nthis castle for much longer.

As this castle had fallen once before,
I was hoping our enemy might turn
a blind eye to it. It seems this line
of thinking was overly optimistic.

This place used to symbolize the hope
we all had, yeah? And if folks find out
yer still kickin' around here, that hope
might flare up in 'em again.
I merely stopped by out of happenstance,\nnot with any grand plan.
But no one took it that way.\nNot us, and sure as hell not the Empire.
Hell, it's only 'cause of you that I was able\nto rally all these folks together and get 'em\nto make a stand against the Empire.
This world of despair came about as a\nresult of my own past foolishness.
This is no heroic stand on my part.\nI simply can't run at this late hour.
That's still somethin'.\nAnd it brings us hope.
Hope is an alien concept for me.
Nah, that ain't true. There's hope.\nIn fact, we got an idea on that front.
Zodiark. He can surmount the\nmetaphorical wall of time itself—\nor at least, he should be able to.
Wanna run that by me again?
Ah, I see. If I use his power...
Yes. If my hypothesis proves correct,\nyou should still possess some fragment\nof the power to travel through time.
And you are suggesting I harness\nthat power to return to the past?
But what about the castle?\nWhat about everyone here?
I hate to say it, but it might already be\ntoo late for the folks of this world.
But if you can go back to the beginning\nand fix things THERE? Before all this?\nThat might be our best shot.
And that makes you the last—hell,\nthe only—hope for this world.
The gates are breached!\nThe dragons are here!
We've no chance to stop them now.\nEveryone, run! Flee for your lives!
I will draw them to me that you\nmight make good your escape!
Nope. That's my job. You get outta here.
You are the last remaining hope for the\nentire world—you cannot fall here!
She's right. And I ain't gonna let our last\nlight flicker out in a place like this!
We can afford to lay down our lives here.\nBut you need to live, for there are things\nthat you alone can do.
Now get outta here and make this\ndamn world right again!
My life's just a drop'a spit in a bucket\nif it means puttin' all this behind us.
C'mon, ya damn dragon!\nCome get a piece'a Ranzal!
*pant* *pant* I wonder if any of\nthe others were able to escape?
I do not sense any other people nearby.\nWe should keep our hopes in check.
No! I can't take this anymore!\nWhy did it turn out like this?!
The blame falls to me. And in many ways,\nthis hell is all I deserve.
But they entrusted me with their hopes,\nso I can no longer be allowed the luxury\nof despair—or even death's cold embrace.
I must carry on and attempt to atone\nfor this most unforgivable sin...
